What are the two scenarios where you may need a licence for dealing in capital markets products?,"- The two scenarios are:
  1) When you are dealing in capital markets products for a business or regulated activity that requires a licence; and
  2) When a licence is required by the competent authority to conduct dealings in capital markets products (i.e., the activity falls under a regulated framework that mandates licensing).

